      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "I LOVERAIN (6) held on to finish third last time out over 1300m at this track after leading for much of the way. Was a big winner prior and with the inside gate and 2kg claim, he will be hard to peg back. ITWASONLYAKISS (4) settled well back then came home powerfully to score by a head over 1300m at this track last time out. Will drift back, but should be in the finish again. PRINCE RUBAN (1) didn't get warm in a much stronger contest last time but won well from the pace the one before. Jarrod Todd gets the best out of the gelding and reunites. Best figures measure up nicely. HOTIM ENGLISH (3) missed a whisker in the I LOVERAIN race, making sharp improvement. Has to be considered going on that effort.",
